{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01B95trPR2vH5VRNY6pVyBtE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.barista.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\n     5→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\n     6→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n     7→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n     8→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Message;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.HashMap;\n    11→import java.util.Map;\n    12→\n    13→@ApplicationScoped\n    14→public class BaristaConsumer {\n    15→\n    16→    private final Jsonb jsonb = JsonbBuilder.create();\n    17→\n    18→    // Consumes commands from orders-service (topic: barista-commands)\n    19→    @Incoming(\"barista\")\n    20→    // Publishes order status updates (topic: order-updates)\n    21→    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")\n    22→    public Message<String> makeCoffee(String orderJson) {\n    23→        try {\n    24→            System.out.println(\"[barista] received: \" + orderJson);\n    25→            // Parse whatever orders-service sent (JSON String)\n    26→            Map<String, Object> in = jsonb.fromJson(orderJson, Map.class);\n    27→\n    28→            // Carry through orderId if present (original Quarkus did this)\n    29→            Object orderId = in.get(\"orderId\");\n    30→\n    31→            Map<String, Object> out = new HashMap<>();\n    32→            if (orderId != null) {\n    33→                out.put(\"orderId\", orderId);\n    34→            }\n    35→            out.put(\"status\", \"READY\");\n    36→            out.put(\"from\", \"barista\");\n    37→\n    38→            // Produce clean JSON (no backslashes)\n    39→            return Message.of(jsonb.toJson(out));\n    40→\n    41→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    42→            System.err.println(\"[barista] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + orderJson);\n    43→            // Let the framework nack and surface the error rather than emitting malformed JSON\n    44→            throw e;\n    45→        }\n    46→    }\n    47→}\n    48→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HmoRLh11oBmCPeB59GK9WC","session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"e8575e80-8117-47b3-9ba7-db9a4ae34434"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HmoRLh11oBmCPeB59GK9WC","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Project Overview:\n\nThis is a distributed coffee shop order management system built with Jakarta EE, MicroProfile, and Open Liberty. The project consists of multiple microservices:\n\n1. Architecture:\n- 3 main services: orders-service, barista-service, kitchen-service\n- Common domain models shared via a 'common' module\n- Uses Kafka for inter-service messaging\n- Configured with MicroProfile and Jakarta EE standards\n\n2. Services:\n- Orders Service: Manages order creation and tracking\n- Barista Service: Handles coffee/drink preparation\n- Kitchen Service: Manages food preparation\n\n3. Key Technologies:\n- Java 21\n- Jakarta EE 10\n- MicroProfile 6.1\n- Open Liberty\n- Apache Kafka\n- Postgresql (for persistence)\n- Maven build system\n\n4. Messaging Patterns:\n- Uses Reactive Messaging for event-driven communication\n- Kafka topics for inter-service communication:\n  * barista-commands\n  * kitchen-commands\n  * order-updates\n\n5. Configuration:\n- Uses MicroProfile Config for externalized configuration\n- Dockerized deployment with Maven/Liberty integration\n- Environment-aware configuration (dev/prod)\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of the project?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"37bb610a-70b8-41a6-b9d8-91df3f654e07"}
