{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VVGBkhYTL51wSDx6jrGrHT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.api;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→\n     6→@ApplicationPath(\"/api\")\n     7→public class OrdersApplication extends Application {}\n     8→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"2c74d3f6-0d27-4cc6-ac30-8570d245e5a2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BJ4GWPUHVMoAShmxwqTegD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.api;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderAck;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\n     5→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\n     6→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\n     7→import com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    12→\n    13→@Path(\"/orders\")\n    14→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    15→@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    16→public class OrdersResource {\n    17→\n    18→    @Inject OrderService orderService;\n    19→    @Inject OrderRepository repo;\n    20→\n    21→    @POST\n    22→    public Response place(OrderRequest req) {\n    23→        String id = orderService.place(req);\n    24→        return Response.accepted(new OrderAck(id)).build();\n    25→    }\n    26→\n    27→    @GET @Path(\"/{id}\")\n    28→    public OrderEntity status(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n    29→        return repo.find(id);\n    30→    }\n    31→}\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"48e480ad-87e8-4897-99c8-e969071a54d5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019PmQt7dW6FQq8sxyBxVxzf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.domain;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.time.OffsetDateTime;\n     5→\n     6→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderStatus;\n     7→\n     8→@Entity\n     9→@Table(name = \"orders\")\n    10→public class OrderEntity {\n    11→\n    12→  @Id\n    13→  @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)\n    14→  private Long id;\n    15→\n    16→  @Column(nullable = false)\n    17→  private String customer;\n    18→\n    19→  @Column(nullable = false)\n    20→  private String item;\n    21→\n    22→  @Column(nullable = false)\n    23→  private int quantity;\n    24→\n    25→  @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)\n    26→  @Column(nullable = false)\n    27→  private OrderStatus status = OrderStatus.PLACED;\n    28→\n    29→  @Column(name = \"created\", nullable = false)\n    30→  private OffsetDateTime created;\n    31→\n    32→  @Column(name = \"updated\", nullable = false)\n    33→  private OffsetDateTime updated;\n    34→\n    35→  @PrePersist\n    36→  void prePersist() {\n    37→    OffsetDateTime now = OffsetDateTime.now();\n    38→    this.created = now;\n    39→    this.updated = now;\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  @PreUpdate\n    43→  void preUpdate() {\n    44→    this.updated = OffsetDateTime.now();\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  // getters & setters\n    48→  public Long getId() { return id; }\n    49→  public void setId(Long id) { this.id = id; }\n    50→\n    51→  public String getCustomer() { return customer; }\n    52→  public void setCustomer(String customer) { this.customer = customer; }\n    53→\n    54→  public String getItem() { return item; }\n    55→  public void setItem(String item) { this.item = item; }\n    56→\n    57→  public int getQuantity() { return quantity; }\n    58→  public void setQuantity(int quantity) { this.quantity = quantity; }\n    59→\n    60→  public OrderStatus getStatus() { return status; }\n    61→  public void setStatus(OrderStatus status) { this.status = status; }\n    62→\n    63→  public OffsetDateTime getCreated() { return created; }\n    64→  public void setCreated(OffsetDateTime created) { this.created = created; }\n    65→\n    66→  public OffsetDateTime getUpdated() { return updated; }\n    67→  public void setUpdated(OffsetDateTime updated) { this.updated = updated; }\n    68→}\n    69→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"d796b227-4686-4ef2-b251-c7176a581dd6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TfMBHqUezs3DpfYgnXysVY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.domain;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     7→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     8→\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class OrderRepository {\n    11→\n    12→  @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"ordersPU\")\n    13→  EntityManager em;\n    14→\n    15→  @Transactional\n    16→  public Long save(OrderEntity e){\n    17→    em.persist(e);\n    18→    return e.getId();\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  public OrderEntity find(long id){\n    22→    return em.find(OrderEntity.class, id);\n    23→  }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"f6170a0a-70ef-4c4d-95b3-72e6c378e952"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FTuugTPmGzf3FjWE5Q5PrZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.health;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheck;\n     4→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheckResponse;\n     5→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.Readiness;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→\n     8→@Readiness\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class BasicHealth implements HealthCheck {\n    11→    @Override\n    12→    public HealthCheckResponse call() {\n    13→        return HealthCheckResponse.up(\"orders-service\");\n    14→    }\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"7cd1b7be-12dd-466d-bdb8-0f4d66e1fc11"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Q96UjUbfL9qQbdJ21CZ5pY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     6→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n     7→\n     8→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderStatus;\n     9→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\n    10→import jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\n    11→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\n    12→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbConfig;\n    13→import java.util.Locale;\n    14→\n    15→@ApplicationScoped\n    16→public class OrderUpdatesListener {\n    17→\n    18→  private static final Jsonb JSONB = JsonbBuilder.create(new JsonbConfig());\n    19→\n    20→  public static final class OrderUpdate {\n    21→    public Long orderId;\n    22→    public String status;\n    23→    public String from;\n    24→  }\n    25→\n    26→  @Inject OrderRepository repo;\n    27→\n    28→  @Incoming(\"order-updates\")\n    29→  @Transactional\n    30→  public void apply(String payload) {\n    31→    try {\n    32→      if (payload == null) return;\n    33→      String json = payload.trim();\n    34→\n    35→      // Unwrap if the payload is a *stringified* JSON object.\n    36→      int safety = 3;\n    37→      while (safety-- > 0\n    38→          && json.length() >= 2\n    39→          && json.charAt(0) == '\"'\n    40→          && json.charAt(json.length() - 1) == '\"') {\n    41→        json = JSONB.fromJson(json, String.class).trim();\n    42→      }\n    43→\n    44→      OrderUpdate evt = JSONB.fromJson(json, OrderUpdate.class);\n    45→      if (evt == null || evt.status == null || evt.orderId == null) {\n    46→        // dev-friendly: ignore malformed/minimal events instead of killing the stream\n    47→        System.err.println(\"[order-updates] ignored event: \" + json);\n    48→        return;\n    49→      }\n    50→\n    51→      var entity = repo.find(evt.orderId);\n    52→      if (entity == null) return;\n    53→      entity.setStatus(OrderStatus.valueOf(evt.status.toUpperCase(Locale.ROOT)));\n    54→\n    55→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    56→      // DEV: log and continue; do not rethrow or the stream will shut down.\n    57→      System.err.println(\"[order-updates] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + payload);\n    58→    }\n    59→  }\n    60→}\n    61→\n    62→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"321fce11-989d-4db8-861d-b0bd9f5b14b1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WiuAPTmNKpXmcHPcrB9xNh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\n     6→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\n     7→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Channel;\n     8→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Emitter;\n     9→\n    10→@ApplicationScoped\n    11→public class OrdersPipeline {\n    12→\n    13→  @Inject @Channel(\"barista\")\n    14→  Emitter<String> barista;\n    15→\n    16→  @Inject @Channel(\"kitchen\")\n    17→  Emitter<String> kitchen;\n    18→\n    19→  private static final Jsonb JSONB = JsonbBuilder.create();\n    20→\n    21→  public void publishToBarista(OrderCommand cmd) {\n    22→    System.out.println(\"[orders] sending barista command: \" + cmd);\n    23→    barista.send(JSONB.toJson(cmd));\n    24→  }\n    25→\n    26→  public void publishToKitchen(OrderCommand cmd) {\n    27→    System.out.println(\"[orders] sending kitchen command: \" + cmd);\n    28→    kitchen.send(JSONB.toJson(cmd));\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  // simple DTO for messages\n    32→  public record OrderCommand(String target, long orderId, String item, int quantity) {}\n    33→}\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"bdcf71b2-a066-4677-ae86-0cdf926af391"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017ac2WKtEjrhHah2rNhxuZY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.service;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\n     5→import com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\n     6→import com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging.OrdersPipeline;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n    10→\n    11→@ApplicationScoped\n    12→public class OrderService {\n    13→  @Inject OrderRepository repo;\n    14→  @Inject OrdersPipeline pipeline;\n    15→\n    16→  public String place(@Valid OrderRequest req){\n    17→    var e = new OrderEntity();\n    18→    e.setCustomer(req.customer());\n    19→    e.setItem(req.item());\n    20→    e.setQuantity(req.quantity());\n    21→    // optional: if you added an enum/string status, default it here (PLACED)\n    22→    // e.setStatus(OrderStatus.PLACED);\n    23→    repo.save(e);\n    24→\n    25→    // simple routing: drinks -> barista, everything else -> kitchen\n    26→    if (isDrink(req.item())) {\n    27→      pipeline.publishToBarista(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"BARISTA\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n    28→    } else {\n    29→      pipeline.publishToKitchen(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"KITCHEN\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n    30→    }\n    31→    return String.valueOf(e.getId());\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  private boolean isDrink(String item) {\n    35→    if (item == null) return false;\n    36→    var s = item.toLowerCase();\n    37→    return s.contains(\"coffee\") || s.contains(\"latte\") || s.contains(\"espresso\")\n    38→        || s.contains(\"cappuccino\") || s.contains(\"americano\") || s.contains(\"mocha\")\n    39→        || s.contains(\"tea\");\n    40→  }\n    41→}\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"4517a692-4281-4a3e-9aba-721ae1e06c6a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Qchrh4HprK1j7xQURXTA3w","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolationException;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.ExceptionMapper;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→import java.util.Map;\n    12→\n    13→@Provider\n    14→public class ConstraintViolationExceptionMapper implements ExceptionMapper<ConstraintViolationException> {\n    15→\n    16→  @Override\n    17→  public Response toResponse(ConstraintViolationException ex) {\n    18→    List<Map<String, String>> errors = ex.getConstraintViolations().stream()\n    19→        .map(this::toEntry)\n    20→        .toList();\n    21→    return Response.status(Response.Status.BAD_REQUEST)\n    22→        .type(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_TYPE)\n    23→        .entity(Map.of(\"errors\", errors))\n    24→        .build();\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  private Map<String, String> toEntry(ConstraintViolation<?> v) {\n    28→    String field = v.getPropertyPath() == null ? \"\" : v.getPropertyPath().toString();\n    29→    return Map.of(\"field\", field, \"message\", v.getMessage());\n    30→  }\n    31→}\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"76982c0f-db22-4d07-a8e7-c76c5e669641"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XSsunLR8EaRJm88ivQ5KdH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n     2→\n     3→import com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\n     4→import com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    15→\n    16→import java.util.Map;\n    17→\n    18→@Path(\"/orders\") // if you already have @ApplicationPath(\"/api\"), change this to just \"/orders\"\n    19→@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    20→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    21→public class OrdersResource {\n    22→\n    23→  @Inject OrderService orderService;\n    24→\n    25→  @POST\n    26→  public Response create(@Valid OrderRequest request) {\n    27→    String id = orderService.place(request); // <-- calls your service\n    28→    // use 202 if you treat it as async, 201 if you consider it created now\n    29→    return Response.accepted(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  @GET\n    33→  @Path(\"/{id}\")\n    34→  public Response get(@PathParam(\"id\") long id) {\n    35→    // if you already have a repository method, reuse it here\n    36→    // shown minimal for completeness\n    37→    return Response.ok(Map.of(\"id\", id)).build();\n    38→  }\n    39→}\n    40→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"a04facf7-998a-4a17-b192-40cc1363683f"}
