{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014BAVjd3sgWx7nPus9XKzsh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_015FN73awaz9gWcjk1hyAS98","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Rewrite orders-service Java files","prompt":"I need you to rewrite multiple Java source files for migrating from Jakarta EE/MicroProfile/Open Liberty to Spring Boot 3.2.5. The project root is at:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__spring/run_3/output\n\nIMPORTANT: The common module files (OrderAck.java, OrderRequest.java, OrderStatus.java) remain unchanged - they use `jakarta.validation` which is correct for Spring Boot 3.x.\n\nPlease write the following files:\n\n### 1. orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/OrdersServiceApplication.java (NEW FILE - Spring Boot main class)\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\npublic class OrdersServiceApplication {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(OrdersServiceApplication.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Rewrite orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/OrdersResource.java\nReplace Jakarta JAX-RS with Spring MVC:\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/orders\")\npublic class OrdersResource {\n\n    private final OrderService orderService;\n    private final OrderRepository repo;\n\n    public OrdersResource(OrderService orderService, OrderRepository repo) {\n        this.orderService = orderService;\n        this.repo = repo;\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping\n    public ResponseEntity<Map<String, String>> create(@Valid @RequestBody OrderRequest request) {\n        String id = orderService.place(request);\n        return ResponseEntity.accepted().body(Map.of(\"id\", id));\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{id}\")\n    public ResponseEntity<OrderEntity> get(@PathVariable long id) {\n        return repo.findById(id)\n                .map(ResponseEntity::ok)\n                .orElse(ResponseEntity.notFound().build());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Rewrite orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/api/OrdersResource.java\nReplace Jakarta JAX-RS with Spring MVC (this is a duplicate endpoint - convert it but make it delegate):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.api;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderAck;\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/orders-alt\")\npublic class OrdersResource {\n\n    private final OrderService orderService;\n    private final OrderRepository repo;\n\n    public OrdersResource(OrderService orderService, OrderRepository repo) {\n        this.orderService = orderService;\n        this.repo = repo;\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping\n    public ResponseEntity<OrderAck> place(@Valid @RequestBody OrderRequest req) {\n        String id = orderService.place(req);\n        return ResponseEntity.accepted().body(new OrderAck(id));\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{id}\")\n    public ResponseEntity<OrderEntity> status(@PathVariable long id) {\n        return repo.findById(id)\n                .map(ResponseEntity::ok)\n                .orElse(ResponseEntity.notFound().build());\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWait - both OrdersResource classes would conflict with bean naming. Let me fix: REMOVE the api/OrdersResource.java since web/OrdersResource.java does the same thing. And REMOVE the api/OrdersApplication.java since Spring Boot doesn't need JAX-RS Application class.\n\nActually, let me think more carefully. The web/OrdersResource and api/OrdersResource both handle /orders. In the Jakarta version, both exist but the web one is used (registered through RestApp). For Spring Boot, we only need one. Let me keep only web/OrdersResource.java and delete the duplicate.\n\nHere's what to do:\n\n1. DELETE orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/api/OrdersApplication.java (replace with empty marker or delete)\n2. DELETE orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/api/OrdersResource.java (duplicate, not needed)\n3. DELETE orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/RestApp.java (JAX-RS Application class, not needed in Spring Boot)\n\nFor files to DELETE: overwrite them with a package declaration only to avoid issues, or simply write new content that won't conflict.\n\nActually the cleanest approach: Write the files with the new Spring Boot content.\n\n### Write these files:\n\n**orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/OrdersServiceApplication.java** (CREATE NEW):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.ComponentScan;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@ComponentScan(basePackages = \"com.coffeeshop.orders\")\npublic class OrdersServiceApplication {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(OrdersServiceApplication.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/OrdersResource.java** (OVERWRITE):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.service.OrderService;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/orders\")\npublic class OrdersResource {\n\n    private final OrderService orderService;\n    private final OrderRepository repo;\n\n    public OrdersResource(OrderService orderService, OrderRepository repo) {\n        this.orderService = orderService;\n        this.repo = repo;\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping\n    public ResponseEntity<Map<String, String>> create(@Valid @RequestBody OrderRequest request) {\n        String id = orderService.place(request);\n        return ResponseEntity.accepted().body(Map.of(\"id\", id));\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{id}\")\n    public ResponseEntity<OrderEntity> get(@PathVariable long id) {\n        return repo.findById(id)\n                .map(ResponseEntity::ok)\n                .orElse(ResponseEntity.notFound().build());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/ConstraintViolationExceptionMapper.java** (OVERWRITE - convert to Spring @ControllerAdvice):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.web;\n\nimport jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\nimport jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolationException;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.MethodArgumentNotValidException;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.ExceptionHandler;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestControllerAdvice;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\n@RestControllerAdvice\npublic class ConstraintViolationExceptionMapper {\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(ConstraintViolationException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<Map<String, List<Map<String, String>>>> handleConstraintViolation(ConstraintViolationException ex) {\n        List<Map<String, String>> errors = ex.getConstraintViolations().stream()\n                .map(this::toEntry)\n                .toList();\n        return ResponseEntity.badRequest().body(Map.of(\"errors\", errors));\n    }\n\n    @ExceptionHandler(MethodArgumentNotValidException.class)\n    public ResponseEntity<Map<String, List<Map<String, String>>>> handleMethodArgumentNotValid(MethodArgumentNotValidException ex) {\n        List<Map<String, String>> errors = ex.getBindingResult().getFieldErrors().stream()\n                .map(fe -> Map.of(\"field\", fe.getField(), \"message\", fe.getDefaultMessage() != null ? fe.getDefaultMessage() : \"\"))\n                .toList();\n        return ResponseEntity.badRequest().body(Map.of(\"errors\", errors));\n    }\n\n    private Map<String, String> toEntry(ConstraintViolation<?> v) {\n        String field = v.getPropertyPath() == null ? \"\" : v.getPropertyPath().toString();\n        return Map.of(\"field\", field, \"message\", v.getMessage());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/domain/OrderRepository.java** (OVERWRITE - convert to Spring Data JPA):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.domain;\n\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\n\n@Repository\npublic interface OrderRepository extends JpaRepository<OrderEntity, Long> {\n}\n```\n\n**orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/domain/OrderEntity.java** (OVERWRITE - keep JPA annotations, they're jakarta.persistence which Spring Boot 3 uses):\nKeep it as-is since it already uses `jakarta.persistence.*` which is correct for Spring Boot 3.x.\n\n**orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/service/OrderService.java** (OVERWRITE):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.service;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderRequest;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderEntity;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging.OrdersPipeline;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\nimport org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n\n@Service\npublic class OrderService {\n    private final OrderRepository repo;\n    private final OrdersPipeline pipeline;\n\n    public OrderService(OrderRepository repo, OrdersPipeline pipeline) {\n        this.repo = repo;\n        this.pipeline = pipeline;\n    }\n\n    @Transactional\n    public String place(@Valid OrderRequest req) {\n        var e = new OrderEntity();\n        e.setCustomer(req.customer());\n        e.setItem(req.item());\n        e.setQuantity(req.quantity());\n        repo.save(e);\n\n        if (isDrink(req.item())) {\n            pipeline.publishToBarista(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"BARISTA\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n        } else {\n            pipeline.publishToKitchen(new OrdersPipeline.OrderCommand(\"KITCHEN\", e.getId(), req.item(), req.quantity()));\n        }\n        return String.valueOf(e.getId());\n    }\n\n    private boolean isDrink(String item) {\n        if (item == null) return false;\n        var s = item.toLowerCase();\n        return s.contains(\"coffee\") || s.contains(\"latte\") || s.contains(\"espresso\")\n                || s.contains(\"cappuccino\") || s.contains(\"americano\") || s.contains(\"mocha\")\n                || s.contains(\"tea\");\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/messaging/OrdersPipeline.java** (OVERWRITE):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport org.springframework.kafka.core.KafkaTemplate;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class OrdersPipeline {\n\n    private final KafkaTemplate<String, String> kafkaTemplate;\n    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n\n    public OrdersPipeline(KafkaTemplate<String, String> kafkaTemplate, ObjectMapper objectMapper) {\n        this.kafkaTemplate = kafkaTemplate;\n        this.objectMapper = objectMapper;\n    }\n\n    public void publishToBarista(OrderCommand cmd) {\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[orders] sending barista command: \" + cmd);\n            kafkaTemplate.send(\"barista-commands\", objectMapper.writeValueAsString(cmd));\n        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to serialize barista command\", e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public void publishToKitchen(OrderCommand cmd) {\n        try {\n            System.out.println(\"[orders] sending kitchen command: \" + cmd);\n            kafkaTemplate.send(\"kitchen-commands\", objectMapper.writeValueAsString(cmd));\n        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to serialize kitchen command\", e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public record OrderCommand(String target, long orderId, String item, int quantity) {}\n}\n```\n\n**orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/messaging/OrderUpdatesListener.java** (OVERWRITE):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.messaging;\n\nimport com.coffeeshop.common.domain.OrderStatus;\nimport com.coffeeshop.orders.domain.OrderRepository;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport org.springframework.kafka.annotation.KafkaListener;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\nimport org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n\nimport java.util.Locale;\n\n@Component\npublic class OrderUpdatesListener {\n\n    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    private final OrderRepository repo;\n\n    public OrderUpdatesListener(ObjectMapper objectMapper, OrderRepository repo) {\n        this.objectMapper = objectMapper;\n        this.repo = repo;\n    }\n\n    public static final class OrderUpdate {\n        public Long orderId;\n        public String status;\n        public String from;\n    }\n\n    @KafkaListener(topics = \"order-updates\", groupId = \"orders-service\")\n    @Transactional\n    public void apply(String payload) {\n        try {\n            if (payload == null) return;\n            String json = payload.trim();\n\n            int safety = 3;\n            while (safety-- > 0\n                    && json.length() >= 2\n                    && json.charAt(0) == '\"'\n                    && json.charAt(json.length() - 1) == '\"') {\n                json = objectMapper.readValue(json, String.class).trim();\n            }\n\n            OrderUpdate evt = objectMapper.readValue(json, OrderUpdate.class);\n            if (evt == null || evt.status == null || evt.orderId == null) {\n                System.err.println(\"[order-updates] ignored event: \" + json);\n                return;\n            }\n\n            var entity = repo.findById(evt.orderId).orElse(null);\n            if (entity == null) return;\n            entity.setStatus(OrderStatus.valueOf(evt.status.toUpperCase(Locale.ROOT)));\n            repo.save(entity);\n\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            System.err.println(\"[order-updates] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + payload);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/health/BasicHealth.java** (OVERWRITE - convert to Spring Boot Actuator health indicator):\n```java\npackage com.coffeeshop.orders.health;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.actuate.health.Health;\nimport org.springframework.boot.actuate.health.HealthIndicator;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class BasicHealth implements HealthIndicator {\n    @Override\n    public Health health() {\n        return Health.up().withDetail(\"service\", \"orders-service\").build();\n    }\n}\n```\n\nAlso DELETE the JAX-RS files that are no longer needed:\n- DELETE orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/api/OrdersApplication.java\n- DELETE orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/api/OrdersResource.java  \n- DELETE orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/RestApp.java\n\nFor the DELETE files, just remove them by using bash `rm`.\n\nPlease write ALL of these files now. Use the Write tool for new/overwrite files and Bash rm for deletions.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":617,"cache_read_input_tokens":92574,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":617,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":6773},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"a0333b17-375e-4da3-94b3-1c6380dfd7a0"}
