{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014hiEtfHLmvgC7eFSbwgoKF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.kitchen.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n     5→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.json.Json;\n     8→import jakarta.json.JsonObject;\n     9→\n    10→import java.io.StringReader;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class KitchenConsumer {\n    14→\n    15→    @Incoming(\"kitchen\")          // channel that reads topic: kitchen-commands\n    16→    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")    // channel that writes topic: order-updates\n    17→    public String cookFood(String orderJson) {\n    18→        System.out.println(\"[kitchen] received: \" + orderJson);\n    19→        // Parse the incoming order (so we can carry orderId across)\n    20→        JsonObject in = Json.createReader(new StringReader(orderJson)).readObject();\n    21→\n    22→        // If original event had orderId, propagate it\n    23→        JsonObject out = Json.createObjectBuilder()\n    24→                .add(\"status\", \"READY\")\n    25→                .add(\"from\", \"kitchen\")\n    26→                .add(\"orderId\", in.containsKey(\"orderId\") ? in.getJsonNumber(\"orderId\").longValue() : -1)\n    27→                .build();\n    28→\n    29→        // This returns a real JSON object string: {\"status\":\"READY\",\"from\":\"kitchen\",\"orderId\":...}\n    30→        return out.toString();\n    31→    }\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</s