{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012mngkDzg5dnVwXNAbaPsAN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.orders;\n     2→\n     3→import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\n     4→import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\n     5→import org.springframework.context.annotation.ComponentScan;\n     6→\n     7→@SpringBootApplication\n     8→@ComponentScan(basePackages = \"com.coffeeshop.orders\")\n     9→public class OrdersServiceApplication {\n    10→    public static void main(String[] args) {\n    11→        SpringApplication.run(OrdersServiceApplication.class, args);\n    12→    }\n    13→}\n    14→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015FN73awaz9gWcjk1hyAS98","session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"d0e5faf4-6500-4142-9070-41db59db4896"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015FN73awaz9gWcjk1hyAS98","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All files have been successfully migrated from Jakarta EE/MicroProfile/Open Liberty to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Let me create a summary of what was done:\n\n## Migration Summary\n\nI have successfully migrated all Java source files for the orders-service from Jakarta EE/MicroProfile/Open Liberty to Spring Boot 3.2.5. Here's what was completed:\n\n### Files Created\n\n1. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/OrdersServiceApplication.java**\n   - New Spring Boot main application class\n   - Uses `@SpringBootApplication` and `@ComponentScan`\n\n### Files Rewritten (Jakarta EE → Spring Boot)\n\n2. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/OrdersResource.java**\n   - Converted from JAX-RS (`@Path`, `@POST`, `@GET`) to Spring MVC (`@RestController`, `@PostMapping`, `@GetMapping`)\n   - Changed from `jakarta.inject.Inject` to constructor-based dependency injection\n   - Replaced `Response` with `ResponseEntity`\n\n3. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/ConstraintViolationExceptionMapper.java**\n   - Converted from JAX-RS `@Provider` and `ExceptionMapper` to Spring `@RestControllerAdvice`\n   - Added handler for both `ConstraintViolationException` and `MethodArgumentNotValidException`\n\n4. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/domain/OrderRepository.java**\n   - Converted from manual JPA repository with `@PersistenceContext EntityManager` to Spring Data JPA `JpaRepository` interface\n   - Added `@Repository` annotation\n\n5. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/service/OrderService.java**\n   - Changed from `@ApplicationScoped` to `@Service`\n   - Changed from `@Inject` to constructor-based dependency injection\n   - Added `@Transactional` annotation (Spring's transaction management)\n\n6. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/messaging/OrdersPipeline.java**\n   - Converted from MicroProfile Reactive Messaging (`@Channel`, `Emitter`) to Spring Kafka (`KafkaTemplate`)\n   - Changed from `jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb` to Jackson `ObjectMapper`\n   - Changed from `@ApplicationScoped` to `@Component`\n\n7. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/messaging/OrderUpdatesListener.java**\n   - Converted from MicroProfile Reactive Messaging (`@Incoming`) to Spring Kafka (`@KafkaListener`)\n   - Changed from `jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb` to Jackson `ObjectMapper`\n   - Changed from `@ApplicationScoped` to `@Component`\n   - Added `groupId = \"orders-service\"` to `@KafkaListener`\n\n8. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/health/BasicHealth.java**\n   - Converted from MicroProfile Health (`@Readiness`, `HealthCheck`) to Spring Boot Actuator (`HealthIndicator`)\n   - Changed from `@ApplicationScoped` to `@Component`\n\n### Files Deleted (No Longer Needed)\n\n9. **orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/api/OrdersApplication.java** - Deleted (JAX-RS Application class)\n10. **orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/api/OrdersResource.java** - Deleted (duplicate endpoint)\n11. **orders-service/src/main/java/com/coffeeshop/orders/web/RestApp.java** - Deleted (JAX-RS Application class)\n\n### Files Unchanged (Already Compatible)\n\n- **OrderEntity.java** - Uses `jakarta.persistence.*` which is correct for Spring Boot 3.x\n- **Common module files** (OrderRequest.java, OrderAck.java, OrderStatus.java) - Use `jakarta.validation.*` which is correct for Spring Boot 3.x\n\n### Key Migration Changes\n\n- **Dependency Injection**: From `@Inject` to constructor-based injection\n- **Scope Annotations**: From `@ApplicationScoped` to `@Service`/`@Component`\n- **REST Endpoints**: From JAX-RS to Spring MVC\n- **Messaging**: From MicroProfile Reactive Messaging to Spring Kafka\n- **JSON Processing**: From JSON-B to Jackson\n- **Health Checks**: From MicroProfile Health to Spring Boot Actuator\n- **Repository**: From manual JPA to Spring Data JPA\n\nAll files now use Spring Boot 3.2.5 conventions and are ready for deployment on Spring Boot instead of Open Liberty."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b03f3699-6115-4602-aa3a-188761fea59b","uuid":"10759784-d1c4-42e9-acce-656e3438e5cb"}
